(Description)
Given an integer array nums, return true if any value appears at least twice in the array, and return false if every element is distinct.

--- Solution ---
class Solution {
    public boolean containsDuplicate(int[] nums) {
        HashSet<Integer> once = new HashSet<>();

        for (int i = 0; i < nums.length; i++) {
            if (once.contains(nums[i])) {
                return true;
            }
            else {
                once.add(nums[i]);
            }
        }

        return false;
    }
}

--- Approach ---
(Key point)
The only main concept of this problem was HashSet, which is the set of unique integers.
With the for loop, if the integer of the given array nums was not appeared before, it adds it to the HashSet,
while if the HashSet contains the integer, it returns true.
